“Sun Soaked” watercolor 8x12
SOLD 🔴 

I could feel the warm sun on my neck and shoulders as I painted this watercolor on the southside of Boulder Colorado.
I wasn’t sure what to do with the trunks of the trees, so I left them white, I think that’ll do.

Green is particularly difficult color to use, and this painting I was using CAD, yellow and neutral tint for most of the green. Kept adding red and blue to vary the shades.

#green #watercolor #pleinair #colorado #boulder #painting #artforsalebyartist

“Prospect Street”
Watercolor 11x14

 The Copley Society is presenting an excellent show “Through Hopper’s Lens” this month 
Artists were encouraged to submit artwork inspired by American born painter, Edward Hopper, noted for his fascination with light and his observations of American life. 
Prospect Street in Gloucester, MA  which became a favorite subject for Edward Hopper

“Entering the Fog” Watercolor 12x16
Back from a recent visit to Monhegan Island Maine - what a uniquely beautiful place. I was impressed by the quiet and softness of the morning fog. It blanked the island in the early morning and made my daily walk more solitary….
Bliss….
#monheganisland #watercolor #fog #morning #morningwalk #tonalistpainting #tonalism

“The Nao Trinidad” Watercolor 16 x12
SOLD 🔴

The Nao TRINIDAD is a Spanish-built replica of the 16th-Century flagship of the Magellan-Elcano expedition, the first to sail around the world. The original was the flagship of the Armada del Maluco (1519-1522), captained by Ferdinand Magellan.

What a beautiful vessel - currently on view along the boardwalk in Newburyport….

No day is complete without a taste of the sea…. Lobster roll please

#naotrinidad #magellan #tallships #newburyport #watercolor #pleinairpainting #lobsterroll #brusheswithnature #newenglandwatercolorsociety

Follow me and the other artists by following the tags  #pleinaireaston #PAE2023

“Busy Beach” Front Beach Rockport
Charcoal

Summer seems to be winding down, but the beaches are still busy. One of my favorites is front Beach in Rockport, while it doesn’t have a lot of sand the setting and the backdrop are really beautiful. 
This motif is part of my online drawing class beginning August 15, check my website for details. 
Over the six weeks we look more closely at how the artist sees the world and also delve into practical composition…

“Summers Clouds” watercolor 9x12
AVAILABLE

This past June I painted along the Ottauquechee River outside of Quechee  Vermont while researching “life by the river”. 
Now, summer seems to be transitioning to fall and I am feeling nostalgic looking at the studies I made while exploring Maine and Vermont …this was such a humid day - I quickly faded after a couple of studies. 

A deep pine forest under summer clouds. 
The river slows

“Glow” 
A recent studio piece built on a field study - the second image
I found it a worthwhile project to take a familiar subject - in this case a view along Charles Street in Boston- and to embody it in mood and the atmosphere, and still keep a painterly touch.

“Glow on Charles Street” is part of the small woks exhibition at the Copley Society
